702449f-b.title: Brooklyn: 6th Street (West) - Neptune Avenue
702449f-b.text:
2866 West 6th Street, west side, between Neptune Ave., and Sheepshead
Bay Road, showing The Harvest, formerly the Coney Island House, later
the Oceanic Hotel. It formerly stood, prior to 1921, at Ne. 622 Nep-
tune Ave.
December 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
The same, also showing overhead the Culver (B.M.T) Line.
December 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
The same, another view. Once a railroad ran from this Hotel to the
beach and the Cars left every few minutes to accomodate the guests.
December 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
